  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "DTC Explanation: P060A"
    },
    {
      "type": "dtc",
      "code": "",
      "text": "DTC P060A: ECU internal circuit error (Transmission CPU/Sub CPU)"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Detection principle explanation"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "50_3.0_jpn_11033559_4.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "If some internal abnormality occurs and the PGM-FI ECU continues to have no monitor signal from the sub-CPU for more than a set period of time, or if a communication error continues for more than a set period of time, the PGM-FI ECU judges a failure and stores the DTC."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Detection frequency, detection sequence, detection time required, detection method type, OBD status"
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "rows": [
        [
          {
            "text": "Detection frequency"
          },
          {
            "text": "24-hour (e.g. observation, operation (of a machine), care (of patient))"
          }
        ],
        [
          {
            "text": "Detection order (of the DTC in question)"
          },
          {
            "text": "nashi (Pyrus pyrifolia, esp. var. culta)"
          }
        ],
        [
          {
            "text": "Detection time"
          },
          {
            "text": "2.0 seconds or longer"
          }
        ],
        [
          {
            "text": "Detection method type"
          },
          {
            "text": "1D/C (single detection method), PGM-FI warning light: On"
          }
        ],
        [
          {
            "text": "OBD Status"
          },
          {
            "text": "Normal judgment, failure judgment, not completed"
          }
        ]
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Detection execution conditions"
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "rows": [
        [
          {
            "text": "condition entry",
            "header": true
          },
          {
            "text": "",
            "header": true
          }
        ],
        [
          {
            "text": "Ignition switch/ ENGINE START STOP switch"
          },
          {
            "text": "Ignition ON mode"
          }
        ]
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Failure Criteria"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "When one of the following conditions persists for more than 2.0 seconds"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        {
          "text": "No signal from the sub-CPU."
        },
        {
          "text": "Abnormal signal from sub-CPU."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Estimated Failure Site"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        {
          "text": "PGM-FI ECU internal circuit failure"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Store and clear DTC"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "If the vehicle is determined to be faulty, the PGM-FI warning light comes on and the temporary DTC, DTC and freeze data are stored in the PGM-FI ECU memory."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "If the vehicle is diagnosed and determined to be normal after running consecutive 3D/C runs, the PGM-FI warning light will turn off. In addition, the PGM-FI warning light, temporary DTC, DTC and freeze data are cleared by using the clear command of the scan tool (including HDS) or by removing the 12V battery terminal."
    }
  ],
